import Mathlib

open Set

/-- If U ⊆ ℂ is open and f : ℂ → ℂ is differentiable on U and injective on U, then f'(z) ≠ 0 for every z ∈ U. -/
theorem injective_holomorphic_on_deriv_ne_zero {U : Set ℂ} (hU : IsOpen U) {f : ℂ → ℂ}
  (hf : DifferentiableOn ℂ f U) (hinj : InjectiveOn f U) (z : ℂ) (hz : z ∈ U) :
  deriv f z ≠ 0 := by sorry
